Police in Tlhabane near Rustenburg in the North West have arrested a 32-year-old man for the alleged murder of his 29-year-old girlfriend.
Police spokesperson Sergeant Kelebogile Moleko said that on Sunday the couple was in Mosetlha Street, Tlhabane, when a fight ensued between them.
“It is alleged that the suspect grabbed a knife and stabbed his girlfriend several times on her upper body,” Moleko said. “The girlfriend fell down on the ground. She was certified dead on the scene by Emergency Medical Rescue Service (EMRS) personnel.”
The suspect was arrested and was due to appear in the Rustenburg Magistrate’s Court on Monday on a charge of murder.
